# CompScan — Project Intelligence

## What This Project Is
CompScan is a fully local AI agent built in Rust that observes system activity, detects patterns, and suggests actionable improvements. It runs entirely on the user's machine with zero network egress.

## Key Architecture Decisions
- Rust chosen for performance, safety, and cross-platform support
- redb (not sled) for embedded database — stable 1.0, ACID, pure Rust
- Hybrid AI: rule engine (fast, zero-cost) + Ollama (deep reasoning, optional)
- Trust-level permission system for actions (Low/Medium/High/Critical)
- TUI (ratatui) + Web (axum with embedded HTML) dual dashboard

## Critical Boundaries
- NO network calls except localhost Ollama (127.0.0.1:11434)
- NO telemetry, analytics, or data collection beyond local storage
- NO unsafe code without explicit justification
- ALL new features must be cross-platform or clearly gated with cfg

## Common Patterns
- Models in `src/storage/models.rs`, database in `src/storage/db.rs`
- Rules in `src/analyzer/rules.rs` — follow existing Insight pattern
- Actions in `src/actions/` — always set appropriate RiskLevel
- Platform code uses `#[cfg(target_os = "...")]`
- Error handling: `anyhow::Result` for apps, `thiserror` for library errors

## Build & Test
```
cargo build                    # Debug build
cargo build --release          # Optimized release
cargo test                     # Run tests
cargo clippy -- -D warnings    # Lint
cargo fmt                      # Format
```
